<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id56980c0d-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02" identifier="/us/usc/t14/s524"><num value="524">§ 524.</num><heading> Enforcement of coastwise trade laws</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Officers and members of the Coast Guard are authorized to enforce chapter 551 of title 46. The Secretary shall establish a program for these officers and members to enforce that chapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id56980c0e-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/111/281/tII/s216/a">Pub. L. 111–281, title II, § 216(a)</ref>, <date date="2010-10-15">Oct. 15, 2010</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/124/2917">124 Stat. 2917</ref>, § 100; renumbered § 524, <ref href="/us/pl/115/282/tI/s105/b">Pub. L. 115–282, title I, § 105(b)</ref>, <date date="2018-12-04">Dec. 4, 2018</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/132/4200">132 Stat. 4200</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
